---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="The Margin Theory Newsletter"
  description="Weekly writing for owner-operators who'd rather see further. Read your own machine. Find the money hiding one layer down."
>
  <section>
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 pt-24 pb-12 md:pt-32">
      <div class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-margin-blue font-semibold mb-6">Newsletter</div>
      <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-7xl font-bold tracking-tight leading-[1.05] mb-8">
        The Margin Theory newsletter.
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-white/80 leading-relaxed mb-10 max-w-2xl">
        Weekly. For owner-operators who'd rather see further.
      </p>

      <!-- Beehiiv embed -->
      <div class="p-8 border border-margin-blue/50 rounded-xl bg-white/[0.03] mb-12">
        <div class="mb-6">
          <div class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-margin-blue font-semibold mb-2">Subscribe</div>
          <div class="text-2xl font-bold">Get next week's edition</div>
        </div>
        <script async is:inline src="https://subscribe-forms.beehiiv.com/embed.js"></script>
        <iframe
          src="https://subscribe-forms.beehiiv.com/d73f35e4-3b8f-48f9-96a4-d9ce33548181"
          class="beehiiv-embed"
          data-test-id="beehiiv-embed"
          frameborder="0"
          scrolling="no"
          style="width: 866px; height: 556px; margin: 0; border-radius: 0px; background-color: transparent; box-shadow: 0 0 #0000; max-width: 100%;"
        ></iframe>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="border-t border-white/10">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 py-20">
      <div class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-margin-blue font-semibold mb-4">What you'll read</div>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-10">The method, in public.</h2>
      <div class="space-y-8">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2 text-margin-blue">How to read your own machine</h3>
          <p class="text-white/70 leading-relaxed">
            The leading indicators every founder-led business produces but most operators never see. How to set up the weekly pulse that keeps you finding margin instead of leaving it on the table.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2 text-margin-blue">Where the money hides</h3>
          <p class="text-white/70 leading-relaxed">
            Specific patterns from real client engagements. The Don Julio pattern. The cash-vs-accrual gap. The COGS creep. What to look for and how to trace it five drivers down.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2 text-margin-blue">The method, in public</h3>
          <p class="text-white/70 leading-relaxed">
            Margin Theory is a thinking brand. Every week teaches a piece of the method you can apply to your own business, with no gated content and no paywalls.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="border-t border-white/10 bg-white/[0.02]">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 py-20">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-6">Why this isn't like other finance newsletters.</h2>
      <div class="space-y-4 text-lg text-white/80 leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          Most finance content is written for finance people. This is written for owner-operators. People who built their business with their hands and their gut, and now the business has gotten too big for either.
        </p>
        <p>
          Most founders leave margin on the table by accident. Finding it takes intention. You walk there on purpose.
        </p>
        <p class="text-white font-semibold text-xl pt-2">
          Margin Theory is the weekly walk.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
